{"ticker": "PGY", "company": "PAGAYA TECHNOLOGIES LTD -A", "weight_sum": 1.49, "etfs": ["IZRL"], "is_private": false, "query": "($PGY OR \"Pagaya Technologies\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since:2026-04-28 until:2026-04-29", "n_fetched": 3, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 2, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2049217413598847052", "url": "https://x.com/Chartradamus/status/2049217413598847052", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/Chartradamus/status/2049217413598847052", "text": "$PGY \n\nMinor Wave 3 (of PW1) PT = $22\n\nAfter a savage correction that was painful to many and invalidated the entire LT structure, it appears that Pagaya may be prepared to attempt to produce a new LT Wave set.\n\nCurrently, it appears to be in a Minor Wave 2 correction. It will attempt to form a higher low off the consolidation below that saw a recent base breakout to complete Minor Wave 1 of Primary Wave 1. I project that either the Daily 20MA or Daily 50MA will provide support here alongside the Volume Shelf in the $12s. If able to do so, expect a rise towards $22 for Minor Wave 3 on the road to completing its initial impulse!\n\nAll in all, the goal moving forward is to reclaim supports such as the $18/$22/$26/$33 key levels one at a time, effectively converting resistance to support. It'll be a tough journey, but it's possible if $XLF catches fire alongside names such as $SOFI. Pagaya is fundamentally undervalued and deserves a re-rating, hence the strength in 2025. Sad story that is was crushed for no reason as the company executes nicely.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 0, "replyCount": 3, "likeCount": 18, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1293, "createdAt": "Tue Apr 28 20:01:18 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 1, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049217413598847052", "displayTextRange": [0, 277], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "Chartradamus", "url": "https://x.com/Chartradamus", "t